-- India’s Welspun Gets Funding for 20-Megawatt Solar Plant
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2013-06-20T13:44:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-20/india-s-welspun-gets-funding-for-20-megawatt-solar-plant.html
Welspun Energy Ltd.,  India ’s biggest
developer of solar projects, arranged 1.35 billion rupees ($23
million) of debt funding for a 20-megawatt plant in Maharashtra
state in the west of the country.  Power from the 1.8 billion-rupee plant in Solapur, about
250 miles (400 kilometers) east of Mumbai, will be sold to
state-run distributor Brihanmumbai Electric Supply & Transport
Undertaking, Welspun said today in an e-mailed statement. It
didn’t identify any of the lenders.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  